Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["5.2 Predicting sequences", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780135559838806*^9, 3.780135566942575*^9}, {
  3.780137123372614*^9, 3.780137125676594*^9}, {3.814450487244215*^9, 
  3.8144504879662848`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0e8ef00b-6f6a-4613-8953-\
c2de2a1c2f52"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This section deals with the prediction of the next value in a sequence. For \
instance, this is plays an important role in language modeling (e.g. \
predicting the next word in a text). Here, we cover some basic concepts. In \
the course on statistics and time series you will see more on prediction of \
time series.\n\nIn Wolfram Language, sequence prediction can be done with the \
function ",
 StyleBox["SequencePredict", "CodeText"],
 ". The usage of this function will be illustrated with several simple \
examples. The examples will be used to give a brief introduction to the \
theory behind sequence prediction."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.777463064670335*^9, {3.780135579518903*^9, 3.780135657726614*^9}, {
   3.780137175292262*^9, 3.780137202477046*^9}, {3.8146284840078297`*^9, 
   3.814628777721633*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8d278b2b-f36a-4bc6-82ca-\
de153c3f23d6"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Simple example 1 - One sequence", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780137155228189*^9, 3.780137160156562*^9}, {
  3.814439989967469*^9, 3.814439997190299*^9}, {3.81462566587086*^9, 
  3.814625679724227*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81b298f2-a935-48cf-b8f4-\
8c18404afd5c"],

Cell["\<\
Suppose that we observed the following sequence of sunny (\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]S\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) and cloudy (\
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]C\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]) days:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.780144381641467*^9, 
  3.7801444102975283`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"aff21ef2-96cf-4083-9f89-\
67e96ffc89f1"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"spSC", "=", 
  RowBox[{"SequencePredict", "[", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
     "\"\<C\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", 
      "\"\<C\>\"", ",", "\"\<C\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", 
      "\"\<S\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\"", ",", "\"\<S\>\""}], "}"}], "}"}], 
   "]"}]}]], "Input",
